## Development Guidelines

### Liquid Templates
- Use `.liquid` extension for templates
- Follow Liquid syntax: `{{ }}` for output, `{% %}` for logic
- Use snippets for reusable code: `{% render 'snippet-name' %}`
- Always check object existence before accessing properties

### Sections
- Located in [theme/sections/](mdc:theme/sections/)
- Include schema for theme editor customization
- Use blocks for repeatable content
- Follow naming conventions: kebab-case

### Styling
- Main stylesheet: [theme/src/styles.css](mdc:theme/src/styles.css)
- Use BEM methodology for class naming
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use CSS custom properties for theming

### JavaScript
- Located in [theme/assets/](mdc:theme/assets/)
- Use ES6 modules or IIFE pattern
- Handle Shopify objects via global window object
- Use AJAX for cart operations

### Performance
- Optimize assets (minify, compress)
- Use lazy loading for images
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Monitor Core Web Vitals

### Accessibility
- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation support

## Quick Commands
```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Build theme
npm run build

# Watch for changes
npm run watch

# Deploy to Shopify
shopify theme push
```

## Best Practices
- Always test across different devices
- Follow Shopify's coding standards
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Document complex logic
- Keep code modular and reusable
- Optimize for performance and accessibility
